# Bunny Glow-Up
### @preferredEditor asset




## {Introduction @showdialog}

Give the bunny a glow-up!

This quick tutorial will show you how to design your own character for an amazing bunny swap.

![Design the Clovers game in simulator](/static/tutorials/bunny/bunny1.gif)



## {Step 2 - Play the OG}

**For a preview of what your swap might look like, open the game window and press the (A) and (B) buttons.**

- :mouse pointer: When you're done playing, click **Next** to get to the next instruction.

![This is where to find the game](/static/tutorials/bunny/bunny-game.gif "Click the game tab above the instruction window")




## {Step 3 - Design the Hero Character}

**Make it your own!**

- :mouse pointer: Click on the white bunny called **Glow-Bunny-Yours** and choose
**Edit** from below the **Asset Preview** pane.

![This is where to find the bunny](/static/tutorials/bunny/bunny-image.png "Look for the white bunny")

- :paint brush: Change the bunny in any way you want or delete the bunny altogether and draw something
new.

- :mouse pointer: When you're happy, click **Done** to go back out to the **My Assets** window.




## {Step 4 - Play Again}

**Play your game again.**

 Test the game with your new art.

 Don't forget to press (A) and (B) to go back and forth between characters.




## {Step 5 - Design More}


- :paint brush: Want to change more?  You can also play around with the **Standard-Bunny** and the **sparkle** background animation.

- :mouse pointer: When you're done, test your game again and see how you like it!




## {Step 6 - Finale}


Change the art as many times as you want. Once you're happy with your game,
click **Done** to share your glow-up with friends!
